premise_source_doc_sentence: While the social sciences sometimes approach gender as a social construct , and gender studies particularly do , research in the natural sciences investigates whether biological differences in males and females influence the development of gender in humans ; both inform debate about how far biological differences influence the formation of gender identity .

Additionally , the terms `` common gender '' and `` epicene gender '' are used to classify ways in which grammatical gender interacts  (  or not  )  with `` natural gender ''  (  the sex of a person or animal  )  .
Gender-based price discrimination is a form of economic discrimination that occurs when one gender is charged a different price than another gender for identical goods or services .
Gender can also be broken into three categories , gender identity , gender expression , and biological sex , as Sam Killermann explains in his Ted X Talk at the University of Chicago .
Epicene  (  epiceno  )  : `` Epicene gender '' is the term applied to those nouns that have only one grammatical gender , masculine or feminine , but can refer to a living creature of either sex .
